The Osun State Police Command has declared Ifeoluwa Bamidele wanted for the alleged murder of her husband; Bolu Bamidele. The Police disclosed this in an announcement made available by Yemisi Opalola, the Command spokesperson, Ifeoluwa committed the act on Sunday, July 17, 2022, at 11:30pm at Kola, Obokun local government. According to Opalola, Ifeoluwa who also goes by the name Akanji Ifeoluwa Haddasah alleged that her husband, Cairo-based Bolu had impregnated another woman and in anger set him on fire. She added that he was initially rushed to Osogbo Central Hospital but later referred to the University College Hospital, Ibadan for specialised treatment. Opalola hinted that the Command in an effort to arrest the fleeing wife had launched a manhunt for her. The Osun police spokesperson also denied news that the wife, Ifeoluwa had committed suicide. Investigations also revealed that Ifeoluwa had left an angry note on her WhatsApp which stated that her husband drove her to the edge. “I’ve always been a calm girl and I’ve never done this in my life but Teebam has pushed me to the edge,” the alleged WhatsApp note reads. “At this point y’all will weep over myself and him before daybreak. I’m promising y’all that!!!” A message obtained from Opalola on Wednesday later revealed that the victim, Bolu Bamidele eventually died at UCH, Ibadan around 4pm on Tuesday, July 19, 2022.